The article describes President Joe Biden welcoming the 2021 World Champion Atlanta Braves to the White House. Biden jokingly mentions that his wife is a Philly fan and congratulates the team on their victory over the Phillies the previous night. He recognizes and introduces several guests from Atlanta, including former Mayor Keisha Lance Bottoms and Mayor Andre Dickens. Biden praises the Braves' history and their legendary player, Hank Aaron. He commends the team for their resilience and perseverance in winning the championship, despite facing challenges and being counted out by many. Biden also highlights the team's community service efforts and their impact off the field. The President concludes by expressing his honor to host the Braves and invites the team's President of Baseball Operations, Alex Anthopoulos, and manager, Brian Snitker, to present a special gift to him.